It's a simple http server (not complete yet)


Dir doc is used for testing "http_show_dir" function

MutiProcess and MutiThread(ThreadPool) works well. Walker support cmd option.
-m on/off  #MutiProcess on or off

-r /path/to/root  #change the default root dir

-c /path/to/cig-bin #change the default cgi dir

-p portnumber   #change the listen port, default to 80 and 
                #you have to run as root

-l load   #not used yet.Further version will use IPC and the option will be used

-n processnumber

-t timeout  #connection timeout, not used yet

-h threadnumber # threadnumber in ThreadPool, set zero to shutdown ThreadPool 

